# Complexity and size

| Metric | Limit |
|--------|-------|
| Cyclomatic complexity | max 10 (ideal ≤ 5) |
| Lines per function | ≤ 30–40 |
| if/loop nesting | max 3 levels |
| Lines per file | ≤ 300–400 |

Above limits: extract sub-functions, Strategy/Polymorphism, early return/guard clauses.

Configure project linter to fail above these limits when supported (ESLint complexity, SonarQube, Radon, etc.).

# Anti king files

**Forbidden** "god" files that everything depends on:

- Giant `utils`/`helpers` used by all domains
- Route file with hundreds of endpoints
- Monolithic config mixing domains

## Warning signs

- File > 400 lines → split by responsibility/feature
- High fan-in (imported by dozens of modules across domains) → split by bounded context

## Legitimate shared code

Base types, VO primitives, infra clients: small, stable, well tested. Changes require broad suite covering all consumers.

Config/env/constants: separate per domain/module, not a single global file.
